{"id": 243345128, "title": "Afrinvest To Continue Partnership With Rangers", "text": "Officials of Afrinvest West Africa Limited, the ma-jor shirt sponsors of the 2023/2024 NPFL cham-pions, Rangers International F.C of Enugu, has affirmed that they would extend their partnership with the club that will campaign for honours in next season\u2019s CAF Champions League. Dr. Ike Chioke, the Group Managing Director of the fi-nancial investment institution, who made this known at a me-dia briefing in Enugu during the week, praised the efforts of management, coaches, players, and backroom staff for their doggedness in winning the league just under one year of his company\u2019s partnership with the club stressing that it was a sign of bigger things to come from the partnership. \u201cWhen in October 2023, we signed this partnership; we de-sired to take Nigeria football to the next level. I am as shocked as everyone that we are already celebrating a big trophy like the NPFL title within the first year of the partnership. \u201cI want to congratulate the G.M. and his lieutenants as well as the Enugu state government for all the support extended to the team. \u2018This trophy is a foundation for growth and from here we can take Nigeria football to the next level. For us at Afrinvest, we are committed to Rangers and re-main steadfastly behind them as they go to represent Nigeria in the CAF Champions League,\u2019 stated the G.M.D of Afrinvest West Africa. Rangers G.M/CEO, Amobi Ezeaku Esq, thanked Afrinvest for their belief and trust in the club, which made them commit their financial muscle to part-ner with the eight-time Nigeria league champions. \u201cI must start by thanking the governor of Enugu state, Dr. Pe-ter Mbah for being a strong pillar of support for the club and spe-cial thanks to the company that believed in us even before we kicked the ball, a company that has shown commitment, Afrin-vest West Africa.", "summary": "<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"><img width=\